SYNOPSIS
	varargs void register_auto_obj(mixed xObj, string sParam)

DEFINED IN
	player.c

DESCRIPTION
	Adds an object to a players autoload list. '<xObj>' may be either
	a string containing the pathname to the object, or the object itself.
	An optional string '<sParam>' can be passed to give starting parameters
	for the autoloading object when it is created on player login.

	NOTE: '<sParam>' really only needs to be passed if '<xObj>' is passed
	      as an object. If '<xObj>' is passed as a string, the starting
	      parameters can be added by simply putting ':<parameters>' on
	      the end of the string.

	When a player logs in, everything in their autoload list will be cloned
	and have the function 'init_arg' called in them with whatever starting
	parameters are supplied.

EXAMPLE
	// This first example will add an autoload by using a string path
	// and an initial starting parameter of "justloading"
	this_player()->register_auto_obj("/objects/hat:justloading");

	// This second example will add an autoload by using an object
	// and an initial starting parameter of "justloading"
	object oHat = clone_object("/objects/hat");
	this_player()->register_auto_obj(oHat, "justloading");

